   Now, if you spend your days raiding Hate, Fear, etc, as the only Chanter there, you might wish your spec was Conjuration to help with all the mezing you will be doing.  But if that is the case, then it would be easier just to find some other Chanters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/umassagran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Massagran</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#330000>(4/16/02 5:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=34.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://massa.aztecaonline.net/minimassa5.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specialization</span><hr size=1> i am conjuration specialized. Ive tried conjuration only cause i think that can help a lot in combat situation. Yep, most of our spellbook is alteration oriented, but a buff wont save your group in a bad pull. And when 2 high level mobs are slashing you, u will die in a fizzle... <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87742">Massagran Menteaudaz</b></a>,  eru enc  50 agnóstico<br>
